<title>USA: Acacia acquires control of Soundview Tech.</title>
<headline>Acacia acquires control of Soundview Tech.</headline>
<dateline>PASADENA, Calif. 1997-07-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>Acacia Research Corp Monday said it has acquired a majority ownership stake in Soundview Technologies Inc in a deal valued at $4.2 million.</p>
<p>Acacia boosted its 16.4 percent stake to a total 51.4 percent of the company by acquiring 35 percento Soundview's shares in exchange for 400,000 Acacia common shares, $500,000 in cash and a $900,000 note.</p>
<p>Soundview owns technology relating to implementing the so-called V-chip, a television feature that allows parents and other viewers to block programs they think are inappropriate.</p>
